tmux execution model (follow exactly):
1) Default mode: use the existing default managed shared pane. Omit `target`, `session`, and `pane`.
2) If you need extra workspace, create an additional pane in the default managed session (`tmux-create-pane`).
3) Only create extra sessions for exceptional isolation needs.
4) Never run tmux lifecycle commands through `run_shell`; use tmux management tools instead.
5) Use `target` only as a legacy escape hatch when you already know an exact tmux target like `%7`.
6) If a tmux tool reports "tmux target not found", retry once with no `target`/`session`/`pane`.

